<div class="rebranding_container block-flex-wrap block-gap-50">
  <div class="article_columns-wrapp block-flex-wrap block-gap-50 block-flex-start-start">
    <div class="article_column article_column-half article_column-text-half block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center">
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100 tal">Examining the logo and stamping</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          The logo and stamping on a Louis Vuitton handbag are crucial indicators of its authenticity. The classic monogram pattern features interlocking LV initials, with the V slightly above the L, creating a perfectly symmetrical design. Any deviation from this symmetry, such as crooked letters or uneven spacing, is a red flag.
          <br><br>
          The stamping on the handbag should be clear and precise, with no blurry or smudged letters. Louis Vuitton uses a unique blend of Futura and Austin Roman fonts for their logo and stamping, which is exclusive to the brand. Ensuring these details are correct is essential in verifying the authenticity of a Louis Vuitton handbag.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-half article_column-text-half block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center">
        <h2 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100 tal">Inspecting the bag’s interior</h2>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Inspecting the interior of a Louis Vuitton handbag is essential to determining its authenticity. The interior should be made of high-quality materials, such as luxurious fabrics or leathers, reflecting the brand’s commitment to exceptional quality. The stitching inside the bag should be precise and even, with no loose threads or uneven seams. 
          <br><br>
          Additionally, authentic Louis Vuitton handbags feature a unique serial number or date code, which can be used to verify the handbag’s authenticity. This code is typically stamped on the interior tag or lining. The interior should also have a distinctive smell, often described as a combination of leather and fabric, which is another hallmark of an authentic Louis Vuitton handbag.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

